
[1]agalmatolite

   AGALMAT'OLITE,n. [Gr. image, and stone.]

   A name given by Klaproth to two varieties of the pierre de lard, lard
   stone, of China. It contains no magnesia, but otherwise has the
   characters of talck. It is called in German, bildstein, figure-stone,
   and by Brongniart, steatite pagodite.
